			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I was lookin up the ancient nuke, and then i got to thinking.  Why is our ancient a nuke?  The ratio isn't all that impressive, hell if you compare it to FBoT its not even that good. (you can compare bolts to DDs now, considering you can shoot bolts threw mobs, corners, SOLID MATTER, etc).
<br />

<br />
Then i checked out some of the other class ancients.  Wizards get a nuke, shamans get a upgrade to canni, necro's get an upgrade to lich.  Why do we get a nuke?  If we aren't suposed to be the masters of spell DPS, why the hell do they keep shoving ancient nukes down our throats?  How about, oh this might be a silly idea, something ancient thats PET or SUMMONED related.  They so badly want us to not do a lot of nuke dmg, why then do they give us wasteful ancients.  Why can't we get an upgrade to say, mod rod?  Make it a 2 min casting time, double the hp double the mana.  Or a pet buff that makes our pet even better, how about a summoned weapon with a lure based proc for a lot of dmg / hp.  but no, even in OoW up and coming spell line up, our ancient is looking to be a nuke.
