<br />

<br />
Who the hell had Ice Comet back in the day when it required drops off both Vox and Nagafen if I remember correctly?
<br />

<br />
Using a spells rarity is hardly relevant when making comparisons. Even discounting SunStrike the Draughts were vastly more mana efficient than Ice Comet was. Again I will say that the same does not apply to Firebolt.
<br />

<br />
I'd love for one of the people who say that Firebolt as it is now should remain to explain to me why a spell bought off a vendor for 300 plat at lvl 61 should be better in every way than those obtained at lvl 65?
<br />

<br />
Is there any other spell in the game that gets 'upgraded' at later levels but in reality is worse in every way than the lower level spell?
<br />

<br />
I can't think of one offhand as even CH doesn't satisfy those conditions as Holy Light is a better heal in some circumstances, which are quite common in GoD.
<br />

<br />
Sorry but Firebolt does need to have some disadvantages compared to the Lvl 65 DD's, either line of sight restrictions or less mana efficiency, with los been the preferred option as that fits in with the way bolts are supposed to work. The should hit objects in their flight path given they represent a ball of fire travelling from the caster to the target.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=342751" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kirium</a>
<br />
Cestus Dei
